reviews.review_text: pretty dang good but not perfect This is a very nice audience recording of a very hot show. The music is right up front but the recording still captures the high energy in the crowd that night.  Howerver there are some skips, glitches, abnormalities....whatever you want to call them.....during the peak of  a smoking Jack Straw.....the only thing holding it back from a 5 star.

Flaw report This was posted as an error but it is a flaw attribute of this seed.

"D1T1 (jack straw) has multiple mis-tracks due to the source disk having scratches in it or something. just as the fat man is really heating up, the source goes back about a minute or so and then repeats the same section again, it does this twice. 
imo, this schoeps copy is superior to the B&K FOB (smoother sub-low end and not as harsh highs), so it'd be great if we had a flawless copy of this source.

thanks a lot and keep up the great work. this site is fantastic! "
need sum help best jack straw bertha ever nuff said

Jerry and Bruce lead the way! Was in attendance at this, my first MSG show.
Took my older brother, who hadn't seen the dead since Pigpen passed away.  We went out to dinner, and I kept looking at my watch....NY City...we ran late and I've never been LATE TO A DEAD SHOW!!!!!!

Walked in and they were in the middle of Must of Been the Roses.  

End of the first set is great, but the real gem here is the jam following WRS. Jerry and Bruce really gel here and it's a jam I've always remembered as being stellar!  

Enjoy, and thanks for the recording.
